## 1. YouTube Tab — Downloader Pipeline

### 1.1 Concurrent Download Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    Start["_do_start_download()"] --> Init["Init locks: _lock, _excel_lock, _stt_lock<br/>Find highest existing STT number"]
    Init --> Pool["ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers=N)"]
    Pool --> P1["_process_one(idx, url, total)"]
    Pool --> P2["_process_one(...)"]
    Pool --> P3["_process_one(...)"]
    P1 --> Done["as_completed → count OK/errors"]
    P2 --> Done
    P3 --> Done
    Done --> Signal["_sig_dl_done.emit()"]
```

**Key design:** Each [_process_one](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/youtube_tab.py#842-1084) is fully self-contained. Thread safety uses 3 separate locks:

| Lock | Protects |
|------|----------|
| `_stt_lock` | Sequential STT number assignment + folder existence check |
| [_lock](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/youtube_tab.py#506-520) | Counters ([done](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/youtube_tab.py#491-496), `errors`) |
| [_excel_lock](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/youtube_tab.py#506-520) | All Excel file writes |

### 1.2 Single Video Download Flow ([_process_one](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/youtube_tab.py#842-1084))

```
Step 1: get_video_info(url) → metadata (id, title, description, channel_url)
         ↓ fallback: regex extract video_id from URL
Step 2: Auto-detect Excel path (channel_url → excel_folder mapping)
Step 3: Early skip if dl_transcript && Excel status == "Done"
Step 4: STT numbering & folder creation (reuse existing [videoID] folder)
Step 5: Download video/audio (if checked, skip if file exists)
Step 6: Download thumbnail (if checked, skip if file exists)
Step 7: Download transcript (if checked, skip if file exists)
Step 8: Update Excel → Transcript = "Done"
```

> [!TIP]
> **Smart skip logic** — Before downloading anything, the system checks: (1) Excel status for "Done", (2) existing video files in folder, (3) existing thumbnail files, (4) existing transcript files. Each asset is independently skippable.

### 1.3 Folder Naming Convention

```
{STT}_{[videoID]}_{safe_title}/
  ├── {STT}_[{videoID}]_{safe_title}.mp4
  ├── {STT}_{videoID}_thumb.jpg
  └── {STT}_[{videoID}]_{safe_title}_transcript.txt
```

STT is a 3-digit zero-padded counter, auto-incrementing from the highest existing number in the save directory.

