## 2. YouTube Tab — Scanner Pipeline

### 2.1 Two-Phase Scanning

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A["scan_playlist(url)"] --> B["Phase 1: fast ID scan<br/>yt-dlp --flat-playlist"]
    B --> C["Filter out known_ids<br/>(from Excel)"]
    C --> D["Phase 2: detailed fetch<br/>only new video IDs"]
    D --> E["Emit results to tree"]
```

**Phase 1** (`_fast_scan_ids`): Uses `--flat-playlist --dump-json` to get only video IDs — very fast, no full metadata.

**Phase 2** (`_fetch_video_details`): For each **new** video ID, fetches full metadata (title, upload_date, duration, view_count) using yt-dlp `--dump-json`.

### 2.2 Scanner Features

- **Date filtering**: `_spn_scan_months` → calculates `date_after` → passed to yt-dlp for server-side filtering
- **Excel dedup**: Loads `known_ids` from existing Excel → Phase 2 only fetches metadata for genuinely new videos
- **Channel ↔ Excel mapping**: [get_excel_path_for_url(url, excel_folder)](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/yt_downloader.py#114-133) extracts channel name → `{channel_name}.xlsx`

### 2.3 Excel Export & Merge

[save_scan_to_excel()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/yt_downloader.py#L1382-L1464) merges new scan results with existing Excel data:
1. Load existing rows by Video ID
2. Overlay new results (dedup by key)
3. Sort by Published date descending
4. Write with auto-fit column widths
5. Handle `PermissionError` with retry popup dialog

