## 3. Transcript Extraction — 3-Tier Fallback

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    Start["Transcript Request"] --> T1["Tier 1: youtube-transcript-api<br/>(Python library, free)"]
    T1 -->|success| Done["Return formatted text"]
    T1 -->|fail| T2["Tier 2: yt-dlp subprocess<br/>(json3 format, free)"]
    T2 -->|success| Done
    T2 -->|fail| T3["Tier 3: ScrapeCreators API<br/>(paid, API key required)"]
    T3 -->|success| Done
    T3 -->|fail en| T3b["Retry: any language"]
    T3b --> Done
```

### Tier Details

| Tier | Function | Method | Cost |
|------|----------|--------|------|
| 1 | [_get_transcript_api()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/yt_downloader.py#992-1059) | `youtube-transcript-api` library | Free |
| 2 | [get_transcript_ytdlp()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/yt_downloader.py#1061-1169) | yt-dlp `--write-auto-subs --sub-format json3` | Free |
| 3 | [get_transcript()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/yt_downloader.py#1178-1240) | ScrapeCreators REST API | Paid |

**Output format** (all tiers): Inline timecodes [(0:00) text (0:05) more text ...](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/rewrite_style_tab.py#1065-1067)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The transcript text uses inline [(mm:ss)](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/rewrite_style_tab.py#1065-1067) timecodes which are critical for the SRT Chapter Tab's timestamp-based splitting. The `chapter_splitter` later strips these with [_strip_timecodes()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/chapter_splitter.py#886-892) before saving final output.

