## 4. SRT Chapter Tab — Processing Pipeline

### 4.1 Batch Processing Entry

[_start_processing()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/chapter_tab.py#L560-L680) orchestrates:

```
1. Collect checked items (local files + Google Docs)
2. AI classify each item's script_type (if auto_classify enabled)
3. Handle format mismatches (popup dialog)
4. Submit matched items to ProcessController
5. After completion → handle mismatched items
```

### 4.2 Format Classification & Mismatch Handling

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    Items["Selected Items"] --> Classify["AI classify_script_type()<br/>→ top_list / narrative / other"]
    Classify --> Check{"user_type == ai_type?"}
    Check -->|match| Queue["Add to matched queue"]
    Check -->|mismatch| Pending["Add to pending_mismatches"]
    Queue --> Process["ProcessController.start()"]
    Process --> Complete["_on_all_complete()"]
    Complete --> Mismatch{"pending_mismatches?"}
    Mismatch -->|yes| Dialog["Show format warning dialog"]
    Dialog --> Override["User selects per-item overrides"]
    Override --> Process2["Process mismatched items"]
    Mismatch -->|no| Finish["Done"]
```

### 4.3 Single Item Processing ([_do_process_item](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/chapter_tab.py#601-987))

This is the core 4-step pipeline:

````carousel
### Step 1/4 — Split Chapters
```
1. Read transcript file → text_lines
2. Extract chapter_guide (timestamps from header)
3. Choose splitting strategy:
   a. Timestamp-based (if guide has timestamps)
   b. AI marker-based (fallback)
4. Validate: check word count per chapter (min 200 words)
5. Re-split if quality issues detected
6. Save CSV report if issues persist
7. 💾 Checkpoint: save_checkpoint(STEP_SPLIT)
```
<!-- slide -->
### Step 2/4 — Clean & Verify
```
1. Delete old output files (Chapter *.txt, *.json, *_MERGED.txt, etc.)
2. If auto_verify enabled:
   a. verify_chapters() via AI
   b. If timestamp-based split → save report only (don't auto-fix)
   c. If AI-based split → retry with verification feedback
3. 💾 Checkpoint: save_checkpoint(STEP_VERIFY)
```
<!-- slide -->
### Step 3/4 — Punctuate & Save
```
1. If SRT parsed (raw subtitles) → punctuate_chapters() via AI
   - ThreadPoolExecutor parallel processing
   - Length ratio validation (0.5 < ratio < 1.5)
2. 💾 Checkpoint: save_checkpoint(STEP_PUNCTUATE)
3. save_chapters() → individual Chapter files (TXT/MD/JSON)
4. merge_chapters() → single _MERGED.txt file
```
<!-- slide -->
### Step 4/4 — Summary & Excel
```
1. If top_list OR ai_summary enabled:
   → save_summary() via AI (JSON response → per-chapter summaries)
2. delete_checkpoint() on success
3. If excel_update enabled:
   → find_excel_for_video_id() across all .xlsx files
   → update_excel_split_status(video_id, "Done")
```
````

