## 8. Thread Safety & UI Communication

| Pattern | Implementation |
|---------|----------------|
| Background processing | `threading.Thread(daemon=True)` + `ThreadPoolExecutor` |
| UI updates | `pyqtSignal` emissions from worker threads |
| Stop/Pause | `_stop_flag` boolean + `pause_event` (threading.Event) |
| Excel writes | Dedicated [_excel_lock](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/youtube_tab.py#506-520) per download batch |
| STT numbering | `_stt_lock` for atomic counter increments |
| API calls | `APIClient` with endpoint rotation + [stop_check](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/rewrite_style_tab.py#1068-1070) callback |

### ProcessController Pattern (Chapter Tab)

The chapter tab uses a `ProcessController` that provides:
- [start(items, process_func, threads)](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/chapter_tab.py#1027-1036) — dispatches items to thread pool
- [pause()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/chapter_tab.py#1200-1211) / [resume()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/chapter_tab.py#1200-1211) — via `threading.Event.clear()/set()`
- [stop()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/youtube_tab.py#1118-1121) — sets stop flag, cancels pending futures
- Signal callbacks: [on_item_start](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/chapter_tab.py#1027-1036), [on_item_complete](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/chapter_tab.py#1037-1049), [on_item_error](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/chapter_tab.py#1050-1059), [on_all_complete](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/chapter_tab.py#1060-1080)

